                                                            <properties alpha="1" enabled="true" height="NaN" minWidth="10" percentWidth="100" selectable="false" tabCount="0" text="Terms and Conditions regarding Insurance Accident notifications, Contract alterations, premature terminations, damage assessment processes, insurance compensations, grounds{\ n}for rejection, terms of premium payment, consequences of failure to do so, insurance accidents, deductible amounts, conflict resolution mechanisms and other cases are regulated{\ n}by Voluntary Health Insurance Rules approved by the board of “INGO ARMENIA” ICJSC on 27.03.26 that is indivisible part of this Policy, (hereinafter the Rules), as well as RA{\ n}Legislation. The Rules are sent to the Insured’s e-mail mentioned in this Policy and are deemed duly notified.{\ n}This Policy definesthe the Insured’s '' free choice' of licensed medical centers in the Republic of Armenia. Annual medical check-up is provided exclusively at partner medical{\ n}facilities, the complete list of which can be found on the Company's website https://shorturl.at/t5VSQ{\ n}The Insurer shall be entitled to deny payment of insurance compensation if, at the time of the occurrence of the insured event, the Policyholder has any overdue obligations towards{\ n}the Insurer in relation to the payment of the insurance premium. This right shall remain in force until 00:00 on the next working day following the date on which the Policyholder{\ n}fully settles the outstanding insurance premium.{\ n}In the event of termination or early cancellation of this Policy at the initiative of the Policyholder, the Insurer shall be entitled to refund to the Policyholder only the positive{\ n}difference between the total amount of insurance premiums paid for the entire validity period of the Policy and the total amount of insurance compensation paid under the same. If{\ n}the result of such calculation is negative or zero, no refund of the insurance premium shall be made.{\ n}If, at the time of termination or early cancellation of the Policy, there are any outstanding or pending insurance claims under consideration, the Insurer shall be entitled to withhold{\ n}the refund of the insurance premium for the unexpired portion of the insurance period until such claims are fully resolved.{\ n}I hereby give my consent for &quot;INGO ARMENIA&quot; ICJSC (hereinafter referred to as the Insurer) to send inquiries (hereinafter also referred to as Inquiry) to &quot;ACRA Credit{\ n}Reporting&quot; CJSC, &quot;Nork&quot; Technological and Awareness Center for Social Services Foundation, and other credit bureaus regarding the receipt and processing of my personal data,{\ n}for the purpose of concluding a contract with me, without any additional notification to me.{\ n}I also agree that, in response to the submitted Inquiry, any information about me may be provided by personal data processors, including information on my present and past{\ n}financial obligations, employment history (including the name of the organization, legal address, TIN, date of hiring and termination – day, month, year, position, means of salary{\ n}payment), as well as other data necessary for making a decision on concluding an appropriate insurance or other contract with me.{\ n}I agree that in the event of concluding an insurance or any other contract, the aforementioned organizations shall provide the Insurer with the specified information at any time{\ n}during the validity period of the Policy upon Inquiry, and the Insurer shall process such information.{\ n}At the same time, I give my consent for the Insurer to transfer information regarding my financial obligations to the Credit Register of the Central Bank of the Republic of Armenia{\ n}and/or &quot;ACRA Credit Reporting&quot; CJSC.{\ n}" toolTip="" x="0" y="0"/>
